# HashSet Pattern
## Recognition
Use HashSet when:
* Need duplicate detection
* Need O(1) lookup
* Need existence checking
* Need unique elements
---
# Core Idea
A set stores only unique values.
```python
seen = set()
```
Operations:
```python
x in seen      # O(1)
seen.add(x)    # O(1)
seen.remove(x) # O(1)
```
---
# Template
```python
seen = set()
for x in nums:
    if x in seen:
        return True
    seen.add(x)
```
---
# Problem 1: Contains Duplicate
## LeetCode 217
```python
class Solution(object):
    def containsDuplicate(self, nums):

        seen = set()

        for num in nums:

            if num in seen:
                return True

            seen.add(num)

        return False
```
Complexity:
```text
Time  : O(n)
Space : O(n)
```
