# Problem 2: Valid Sudoku
## LeetCode 36
Idea:
Store:
* Row values
* Column values
* Box values
in sets.
```python
class Solution(object):
    def isValidSudoku(self, board):
        rows = [set() for _ in range(9)]
        cols = [set() for _ in range(9)]
        boxes = [set() for _ in range(9)]
        for r in range(9):
            for c in range(9):
                if board[r][c] == ".":
                    continue
                value = board[r][c]
                box = (r // 3) * 3 + (c // 3)
                if value in rows[r]:
                    return False
                if value in cols[c]:
                    return False
                if value in boxes[box]:
                    return False
                rows[r].add(value)
                cols[c].add(value)
                boxes[box].add(value)
        return True
```
Complexity:
```text
Time  : O(81)
Space : O(81)
```
# Problem 3: Longest Consecutive Sequence
## LeetCode 128
Idea:
Start only when:
```python
num - 1 not in set
```
Then grow sequence.
```python
class Solution(object):
    def longestConsecutive(self, nums):
        num_set = set(nums)
        longest = 0
        for num in num_set:
            if num - 1 not in num_set:
                length = 1
                while num + length in num_set:
                    length += 1
                longest = max(longest, length)

        return longest
```
Complexity:
```text
Time  : O(n)
Space : O(n)
```
